By Cheryl Otstott Custom size paper selections can be created at the machine for copies but we will look at creating custom sizes in the print driver for print jobs. You can save the custom size to be used repeatedly. Let us look at the general steps for creating and saving a custom size for paper in the driver. Your steps may be slightly different depending on the model of your Xerox printer or multifunction printer and the operating system (OS) you are using. Depending on your machine you can print custom-size paper from Trays 1–5. Since custom size paper settings are saved in the print driver they are available for you to select in all your applications. Please check your paper and paper tray specifications for information on the sizes supported for the paper trays on your machine. Custom sizes are most commonly printed from the bypass tray. To create a custom paper size in the Windows print driver: <img class="aligncenter wp-image-314715 size-full" src="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Custom-size-paper.-stepsjpg.jpg" alt="" width="587" height="433" srcset="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Custom-size-paper.-stepsjpg.jpg 587w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Custom-size-paper.-stepsjpg-542x400.jpg 542w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Custom-size-paper.-stepsjpg-583x430.jpg 583w" sizes="(max-width: 587px) 85vw, 587px" /> To print a document on custom size paper using a Windows OS: To create custom paper size in the Apple Macintosh OS X (10.5 or Higher) driver: To print a document on custom size paper using a Mac OS: Those are the basic steps, the steps may differ a little depending on the machine you are using. These instructions are presented to help you to know where to look in your driver for the custom setup. If you need further information or help, please search the online support for your model of machine or contact your local support centre. This article 